Silver Cloud Spur in Newton park. Picture: Fredlin Adriaan Four patrons of Silver Cloud Spur in Newton Park were robbed of their personal belongings on Tuesday afternoon. According to police, the four patrons were seated at the restaurant when one unknown person walked in and sat near to their table. Seconds later, three other people joined him at the table. A waitress was allegedly asked for a glass of water and once she left, three of the men approached the four patrons seated at another table. One person produced a firearm and they demanded money. When the group said that they had none, the men took their bags and walked out. Documents and a cell phone was in one of the bags, police said in a statement. No shots were fired and police are investigating a case of armed robbery. &nbsp; Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share